              <div class="stemson-note">
                <p>Now this is what I call practical engineering. The potato-in-the-exhaust trick is used in field sabotage—it works perfectly by disrupting the exhaust stroke. The water intake clogging? Legitimate. Marine engines are vulnerable to cooling blockages; it's a well-known sabotage vector. The tungsten filament lock pick is clever—lightbulb filaments are tough and precise. This episode demonstrates that MacGyver understands mechanical systems deeply. Pete alongside him makes sense—two professionals executing a clean operation. The caulking adhesive is a reasonable field repair material. Solid work.</p>
