              <div class="science-block">
                <h4>Pressure Distribution and Weight Support</h4>
                <p>A thin board spreads the vehicle's weight across a wider surface area, reducing point pressure on any single spike. The spikes sink into the board instead of the tire. This works because pressure equals force divided by area—distributing weight lowers pressure below the spike's penetration force. Military and law enforcement use similar tactics.</p>
                <span class="formula">Pressure = Force &div; Area</span>
              </div>

              <div class="hack-item">
