                  <span class="hack-verdict plausible">PLAUSIBLE</span>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="science-block">
                <h4>Pressure Vessels and Exothermic Reactions</h4>
                <p>A toothpaste tube can withstand internal pressure if sealed properly. Certain chemical combinations (acids with bases, oxidizers with fuels) produce rapid exothermic reactions. A sealed container amplifies the pressure buildup. However, creating a reliable, controllable explosive in a toothpaste tube would require precise chemical knowledge and timing. The concept is theoretically sound but practically dangerous and unreliable.</p>
              </div>

              <div class="hack-item">
