                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="science-block">
                <h4>Simple Machines and Lever Mechanics</h4>
                <p>A ruler is a straight, relatively rigid bar—the basic definition of a lever. With a fulcrum and sufficient length, it can lift or move objects heavier than direct force could handle. Simple machines are the foundation of mechanical advantage. This principle has been used for millennia and requires zero high technology.</p>
